  "scenario-notes": "No custom-resolver in escrow \u2014 avoids Priority 1 exclusive authority. Resolution-module is set to 0xoriginal (single-address module). Governance (role=governance) rotates the dispute-resolver mid-dispute from 0xoriginal to 0xattacker. The attacker resolves with is-release=false (refund to seller, buyer loses). Priority 2 (resolution-module) rejects 0xattacker, but Priority 3 fallthrough (= caller = et.disputeResolver) passes because rotation updated dispute-resolver. Every action is authorized \u2014 zero on-chain fault signals. Matches F3 governance-sandwich.",
